    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Attribute</IRI>
        <Literal>Clinical parameters that define the state of a patient and whose value may modify the evolution of the Disease and/or specific manifestations</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://ontologydesignpatterns.org/opla-sd#entityPosition"/>
        <IRI>#ChronicManifestation</IRI>
        <AnonymousIndividual nodeID="_:genid2147483651"/>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Cost</IRI>
        <Literal>Cost related to any class</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://ontologydesignpatterns.org/opla-sd#entityPosition"/>
        <IRI>#DataItemType</IRI>
        <AnonymousIndividual nodeID="_:genid2147483652"/>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#DetectionIntervention</IRI>
        <Literal>An intervention intended to detect the presence of a disease or condition in a person</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Development</IRI>
        <Literal>Certain progression of a Disease that comprises a specific set of manifestations or a set of pathways to such manifestations</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#DiagnosisIntervention</IRI>
        <Literal>An intervention intended to establish the presence/absence of certain disease or condition</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#DiseaseProgressionPathway</IRI>
        <Literal>The way a manifestation appears. It may be a probability, time to event, a proportion of people affected..., and it may change depending on the Development of the Disease or a specific Intervention</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Drug</IRI>
        <Literal>A natural or synthetic remedy for a disease or manifestation</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#FollowUpTest</IRI>
        <Literal>Tests performed to monitor the state of a patient</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Guideline</IRI>
        <Literal>The way a treatment, drug, test... is applied. It defines a period of time (range), dose, frequency, etc.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#HealthTechnology</IRI>
        <Literal>Any treatment, drug, test... that may be applied to a patient</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Intervention</IRI>
        <Literal>Some kind of treatment, drug, surgical procedure... used to modify the development of a Disease</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal>Symptoms and signs of a Disease. They may be chronic or acute</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Parameter</IRI>
        <Literal>Parameters used for computing outcomes or characterize certain class. They have a source, a geographical context, year, description and value.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#ParameterNature</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">The nature of the values of a parameter, i.e., whether it is a constant, calculated, or characterizes uncertainty somehow</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Pathway</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">The way a disease, development, manifestation or stage appears, i.e., the conditions that must be met to lead to any of these.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#REMOVEhasFrequency</IRI>
        <Literal>Indicates the time cycle of how often the treatment, the follow-up test or their respective strategies have to be applied. In the case of a manifestation of the disease, it will indicate how many times a year the symptom manifests itself. 

By default = 1, for the Manifestations.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#RareDisease</IRI>
        <Literal>A Disease with very low  prevalence</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#ScreeningIntervention</IRI>
        <Literal>An intervention to identifiy the subset of population who may have certain disease or condition and require further testing to obtain a final diagnosis</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#ScreeningStrategy</IRI>
        <Literal>A test used to identify persons potentially suffering a disease among a population</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://ontologydesignpatterns.org/opla-sd#entityPosition"/>
        <IRI>#Stage</IRI>
        <AnonymousIndividual nodeID="_:genid2147483648"/>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Stage</IRI>
        <Literal>A phase or step in the progression of a disease</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Treatment</IRI>
        <Literal>Any non-drug intervention used to treat a disease or manifestation</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#appliesOneTime</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Defines the temporal behavior of a parameter (generally a cost or utility): if true, applies upon onset of some model item (disease, disease progression...); otherwise, it is assumed to apply annually.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#dependsOnAttribute</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Defines a relationship between a Valuable instance and an Attribute, where the &quot;hasExpression&quot; of the domain instance makes reference to the range instance. Hence, the hasExpression property should include a reference to that attribute, so that the final value of this Valuable is a function of the value of this attribute.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#dependsOnParameter</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Defines a relationship between a Valuable instance and a Parameter, where the &quot;hasExpression&quot; of the domain instance makes reference to the range instance. Hence, the hasExpression property should include a reference to that parameter, so that the final value of this Valuable is a function of the value of this parameter.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasConditionExpression</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">It allows expressing conditions based on parameters that we will find in the model. For example, we can find that certain drugs will be administered depending on the weight or age of the patient.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasDescription</IRI>
        <Literal>Description of the cost</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasDose</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Dosage of the indicated drug</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasFrequency</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Indicates the time cycle of how often the treatment, the follow-up test or their respective strategies have to be applied. In the case of a manifestation of the disease, it will indicate how many times a year the symptom manifests itself. 

By default = 1, for the Manifestations.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasHoursInterval</IRI>
        <Literal>Interval in which the indicated dose of drug should be given.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasIncreasedMortalityRate</IRI>
        <Literal>By default = 1</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasInitialProportion</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">The initial proportion of patients of a population that already present certain manifestation</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasProbabilityOfDiagnosis</IRI>
        <Literal>Probability that the manifestation presented, the clinical diagnosis is made.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasRange</IRI>
        <Literal>Age range in which the drug will be delivered.

Examples: 
   0y-2y    =&gt; 0 years to 2 years
   3m-2y   =&gt; 3 months to 2 years</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="#TODO"/>
        <IRI>#hasRiskCharacterization</IRI>
        <Literal>Check if this is the best name for the property</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasSensitivity</IRI>
        <Literal>The Sensitivity in epidemiology is the Probability of correctly classifying a sick individual, that is, the Probability that a positive result will be obtained in a diagnostic test for a sick subject. The Sensitivity is, therefore, the ability of the complementary test to detect the disease. Sensitivity is the percentage of true positives or the Probability that the test is positive if the disease is present; False negatives are sick subjects diagnosed as healthy.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasSpecificity</IRI>
        <Literal>Start Age</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasSpecificity</IRI>
        <Literal>The Specificity of a test is the Probability that a healthy subject will have a negative test result. Specificity is the percentage of true negatives or the Probability that the test will be negative if the disease is not present. False positives are healthy subjects diagnosed as sick.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasTemporaryThreshold</IRI>
        <Literal>Time limit in which the sample must be made. For example on the third day of birth. This value must be expressed in number of days.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#hasYear</IRI>
        <Literal>Year in which the cost data is collected</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#usesSameModelItemsAs</IRI>
        <Literal>Defines that a model uses the same data items as another model. Useful for avoiding &quot;recreating&quot; that relationship for all the model items in models which are very similar and simply difer in some characteristics.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
